 approach, emphasizing the consequences of the Pandemic and their impact on U.S. Foreign Policy. He also argues that if the United States wants to maintain its leadership in the post-pandemic world order, Washington should develop a new concept of smart power to deter the Chinese Art of War. The foremost goal of Pandemics Among Nations is to analyze how America could overcome the geopolitical effects of the Pandemic. The author examines three possible scenarios for the future role of the United States on the post-pandemic Chessboard. The analysis rests on the testing of a series of research hypotheses across a structured comparison of all elements of the remastered Grand Chessboard, not just on isolated case studies such as China’s rise, Russian New Imperialism or European ambitions for a mutual defense.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 4aChina. 4aInternationale Beziehungen. 4aInternationale Ordnung. 4aPandemie. 4aSARS-CoV-2. 4aSoft Power. 4aUSA. 4aWeltordnung. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Geopolitics.2bisacsh  aChessboard.  aInternational Order.  aInternational Relations.  aPandemic.  aSARS-CoV-2.  aUnited States.  aWorld Order.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2022 Englishz978311099451308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2022z9783110994407oZDB-23-PLW0 cEPUBz97831107410180 cprintz978311074075240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311074086840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110740868423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110740868/original  a978-3-